fields.endorsement_text: Kalum is one of the hardest workers I know.  Once he decides to do something, he will always see it through and make sure it's done right.
fields.message: Hey Kalum, I'm getting a few friends onto Villages to test it out.  Let me know what you think, and feel free to invite others.

fields.endorsement_text: Joel is a master adventurer and organizer of large boxes into small closets.
fields.message: Hey Joel.  I'm starting to invite people to Villages.  Check it out and let me know what you think.

fields.endorsement_text: Wes is a naturally talented graphic designer who knows how to get his hands dirty.
fields.message: Hey Wes.  Here's my new site.  Check it out and let me know what you think.  I think I've got a pretty solid basic layout that could use some finishing.

fields.endorsement_text: Heather is smart, caring, and lots of fun to hang out with.
fields.message: Hi Heather.  Here's the site I've been working on for quite some time.  When you get a chance, I'd appreciate if you could give it a go and let me know what you think.  Thanks.

fields.endorsement_text: Jessica is a talented oboist and music educator with blossoming conducting skills.
fields.message: Hi! A friend from high school just created this website and it seems like a cool idea.

Hi Carl,
Please come and check out my friend Ryan's really useful website. It's up and running now, and has at least a couple of users in your neighbourhood.
-hjh

fields.endorsement_text: Patrik is a genuinely brilliant soul who has been promoting sustainability and grassroots community projects for years.
fields.message: Hey Pat this check out my friend Ryan Fugger's villages community an exciting barter based project

fields.endorsement_text: My Dad <3
fields.message: Hey Dad.  Here's an invitation to my site.  Check it out and let me know your impressions.  Also, try to invite Lynda and let me know if that process seems clear enough for you.  Feel free to invite whoever you want.  Thanks!

fields.endorsement_text: Russ and Kathy are great people who have a great talent for designing kitchens and bathrooms.
fields.message: Ryan Fugger has just started up this website, so I am inviting you to help him get it started.

Becca, you've got to check out Villages! 

It's an economic system that uses acknowledgements between friends rather than money to keep score. Developed by my friend (our friend?) Ryan Fugger, it's a great way to trade goods and services directly with one another, find trustworthy people to collaborate with, and promote what you have to offer to your community. Come see!
Vicki

Come join us on Villages! This is the project Ryan Fugger developed that he and I were telling you about. fields.endorsement_text: Flo is a community organising demon from hell or at least the far end of Tilly Road.
fields.message:
Hi Flo,

OK it's here. You won't find much that is useful on here yet but I'd highly encourage you to get involved lets see if we can do timebanking - but in a viral way!

When I invited you I am also offering you to have up to 3 hearts or 'three hours of value' I'm willing to provide in return in return for acknowledgements.. Yeah sounds about right I could do that.
Here's your invitation...

fields.endorsement_text:
Igor é um colega de piso e amigo genial. Boa pessoa.
Acho que é bom em marketing.
fields.message:
Olá, Igor.
Olha este site. Acho que é uma cena bue de fixe. Mas ainda nao há muita gente. Vais ter tú que convidar mais gente para o poder utilizar.

fields.endorsement_text: Perdón por no describir a este amigo personalizadamente como se merece. Lo haré dentro de poco.
fields.message:
Qué pasa peña?
Os invito a la página esa de la que os he estado hablando, por si un dia le quereis echar un vistazo y tal. Además, os doy a cada uno un corazón. Osea, me puedes dejar a fiar (en cosas que me compres a mi o a amigos mios) hasta 1 hora.
Debería poneos un un mensaje personalizado sobre lo que hacéis bien y lo mucho que moláis, pero creo que voy a invitar a mucha gente y no sé si muchos le vais a hacer siquiera caso a la página.
A ver quién es el primero en dar o recibir un Acknowledgement (una hora).
La verdad es que hasta que no haya más gentecilla, parece difícil.

fields.endorsement_text: Perdón por no describir a esta amiga personalizadamente como se merece. Lo haré dentro de poco.
fields.message:
Hola,
Te invito a esta página que me parece muy interesante. En realidad creo que puede cambiar el mundo a largo plazo, pero veamos primero qué puede hacer por nosotros ahora.
El sitio te permite comprar cosas y sobre todo, servicios de otras personas sin necesidad de usar dinero.
Tampoco es gratis, tú también tienes que compartir tus habilidades con los demás.
Te pongo un ejemplo, para que entiendas cómo funciona por dentro:

Ana es amiga de Bernardo, que es amigo de Carlos, que es amigo de David, que es muy bueno en matemáticas.
Ana no conoce a David, pero ve el anuncio en la página "clases de matemáticas" y David le da una clase.
David le ha echo un favor a Carlos, que ha podido hacerle el favor a Bernardo de hacerle el favor a Ana.
Pero David le debía un favor a Carlos, así es que entre ellos dos no tienen cuentas abiertas.
Ana tiene un huerto y anuncia pimientos y patatas en la página. A Carlos le gusta la idea y decide saldar así el favor que le debe Bernardo, a quien a su vez le debe un favor Ana.
Nadie debe favores a nadie ahora.
Luego Bernardo, que es muy bien cocinero, le prepara unos tuppers a David, que tiene poco tiempo para comer a medio día; Emilio es fotógrafo y ayuda a Bernardo a fotografiar sus platos; Felipe deja a su hijo en casa de David, que también le dá clases al niño; Gerardo no consigue cambiar el condenado timbre de su casa, que está estropeado y llama a su amigo Felipe, que es un manitas, etcétera.  

Además de invitarte, te doy un corazón. Eso significa que me puedes "dejar a deber" (en cosas que me compres a mi o a amigos mios) hasta 1 hora.
Sí, no lo había dicho. Los favores se cuentan en horas, no en euros. Se supone que es una hora de trabajo no cualificado. Osea, seguramente el médico querrá cobrar más de 1 hora de la página por una hora de su trabajo. De cualquier manera, las dos partes tienen que estar de acuerdo en el "precio en horas" de cada favor.
Como yo te he dado un corazón, tú puedes pagar a mis amigos, yo respondo por ti.
Además, tus amigos me pueden pagar a mi. Te lo dirán: "te debo un favor, que el dice que confia en que tu le pagarás por mi". 
Si quieres que yo pueda pagar a tus amigos, puedes darme un corazón o varios a mi. El número de corazones indica el número máximo de horas.
Eso también permitirá que mis amigos puedan pagarte a ti. Si luego no quieres nada de ellos a cambio del favor que les hagas, yo te compensaré.

Debería poneos un un mensaje personalizado sobre lo que hacéis bien y lo mucho que moláis, pero creo que voy a invitar a mucha gente para promover la página y no sé si muchos le vais a hacer siquiera caso a esto.
A ver quién es el primero en dar o recibir un Acknowledgement (una hora).
La verdad es que hasta que no haya más gentecilla, parece difícil. Pero tenemos que intentarlo.
Un comercio más justo y menos dependiente de los bancos es posible.
Demos un primer pequeño paso.

Nadie debe favores a nadie ahora.
Luego Bernardo, que es muy bien cocinero, le prepara unos tuppers a David, que tiene poco tiempo para comer a medio día; Emilio es fotógrafo y ayuda a Bernardo a fotografiar sus platos; Felipe deja a su hijo en casa de David, que también le dá clases al niño; Gerardo no consigue cambiar el condenado timbre de su casa, que está estropeado y llama a su amigo Felipe, que es un manitas, etcétera.  

Además de invitarte, te doy un corazón. Eso significa que me puedes "dejar a deber" (en cosas que me compres a mi o a amigos mios) hasta 1 hora.
Sí, no lo había dicho. Los favores se cuentan en horas, no en euros. Se supone que es una hora de trabajo no cualificado. Osea, seguramente el médico querrá cobrar más de 1 hora de la página por una hora de su trabajo. De cualquier manera, las dos partes tienen que estar de acuerdo en el "precio en horas" de cada favor.
Como yo te he dado un corazón, tú puedes pagar a mis amigos, yo respondo por ti.
Además, tus amigos me pueden pagar a mi. Te lo dirán: "te debo un favor, que el dice que confia en que tu le pagarás por mi". 
Si quieres que yo pueda pagar a tus amigos, puedes darme un corazón o varios a mi. El número de corazones indica el número máximo de horas.
Eso también permitirá que mis amigos puedan pagarte a ti. Si luego no quieres nada de ellos a cambio del favor que les hagas, yo te compensaré.

Debería poneos un un mensaje personalizado sobre lo que hacéis bien y lo mucho que moláis, pero creo que voy a invitar a mucha gente para promover la página y no sé si muchos le vais a hacer siquiera caso a esto.
A ver quién es el primero en dar o recibir un Acknowledgement (una hora).
La verdad es que hasta que no haya más gentecilla, parece difícil. Pero tenemos que intentarlo.
Un comercio más justo y menos dependiente de los bancos es posible.
Demos un pequeño primer paso.

fields.message: it's ripple
Tiene buena pinta, joven pero con muy buena pinta.

Hola, bienvenido a la página.
Te pego aquí el texto que le he puesto a algunos amigos dentro de un ackowledgement para introducirlos en la página:

Mira, te pago (acknowledgement, reconocimiento) una hora para que veas cómo es.
Normalmente aquí pondría algo como "me ha hecho tal favor". 
Normalmente tampoco podría pagarte, porque tú no no has indicado que confies en mi. Pero estoy haciendo un reconocimiento directo, que sería algo así como "te pago, aunque tú no aceptes esto como pago".
Luego, por favor, devuélveme la hora, para que no se quede ahí que debo una hora más de las que realmente debo en mi total.
Para pagarme tienes que pulsar meterte en mi perfil y pulsar "acknowledge" (izq)

Ahora como máximo tú me puedes deber a mi una hora, porque yo te he dado un endorsement (muestra de confianza, patrocinio) de 1 corazoncito.
A ti no te puede deber nadie (salvo direct acknowledgements), porque tú todavía no confías en nadie.
Para que la gente pueda pagarte a ti en horas de las que tu aceptas, tienes que confiar en alguien. Puedes confiar (dar corazoncitos) en personas que están ya registradas en la página entrando en su perfil y pulsando "Endorse" (izq).
Puedes confiar en personas que no están registradas a la vez que las invitas pulsando "Invite a friend" (der).
Cada corazoncito representa una hora, cuantos más le des a una persona, más confianza muestras y más te compromentes por ella.

Como yo confio en ti, Ryan confía en mi y los amigos de Ryan confían en éĺ, tú ya podrías pagar a todos ellos hasta una hora, que me deberías a mi.
Pero, por favor, espera un poco antes de hacerlo. Vamos a intentar primero hacer cosas por y recibir de gente que tenemos más cerca, porque localmente es mucho más fácil devolver favores. 

Puedes poner un anuncio pulsando "new post" (der). Para diferenciar si es algo que ofreces o que buscas, hay una casilla que debes marcar cuando el anuncio es por algo que buscas.
Puedes ver los anuncios de otros si pulsas "feed" (izq) y después "Posts" (arriba)
Pregúntame si tienes alguna duda.

Hi Jo,

Please check out Villages. I think you'll like it. Basically, it's a network that facilitates trade of goods and services among people within a community, without the need for money. If you have goods or services up for offer, please post them. If there are goods or services you need, please post them too. You may recognize a few of the current members. Feel free to invite your friends and colleagues, too.

-Heather

fields.title: Nicotiana Rustica Seeds (Aztec Tobacco)
fields.text:
Ornamental use only - not for consumption. Plant responsibly. 

Nicotiana rustica, known in South America as Mapacho, is a plant in the Solanaceae family. It is a very potent variety of tobacco. The high concentration of nicotine in its leaves makes it useful for creating organic pesticides. 

Rustica is also used for entheogenic purposes by South American shamans. Growing in the rainforest it contains up to twenty times more nicotine than common North American varieties such as N. tabacum. Other reasons for its shamanic use are the comparatively high levels of MAOI beta-carbolines, including harman and norharman. 

Nicotiana Rustica has an extremely high nicotine content. The nicotine content can reach as high as 9% giving it some use as a natural organic pesticide. It produces millions of seeds, hundreds of small yellow to greenish flowers, and grows to about four feet tall. This is related to smoking tobacco, and has been used for the same purpose in the past.

fields.title: Nicotiana Sylvestris Seeds
fields.text:
Nicotiana sylvestris is a species of wild tobacco known by the common names Woodland Tobacco and South American Tobacco. It is native to South America, and is often grown in gardens for its scented flowers. The scent is strongest at night, so as to attract pollinating moths. The leaves are simple, somewhat sticky, foul-smelling, with the blade partially surrounding the stem (clasping petiole). Flowers are tubular, white, borne in large clusters above the foliage. Flowers can be over 7 centimeters long with a face 2 centimeters wide. Each flower eventually produces a large quantity of small seeds.


1000 Viable Nicotiana Sylvestris Seeds per packet Nicotiana sylvestris is a species of wild tobacco known by the common names Woodland Tobacco and South American Tobacco. It is native to South America, and is often grown in gardens for its scented flowers. The scent is strongest at night, so as to attract pollinating moths. The leaves are simple, somewhat sticky, foul-smelling, with the blade partially surrounding the stem (clasping petiole). Flowers are tubular, white, borne in large clusters above the foliage. Flowers can be over 7 centimeters long with a face 2 centimeters wide. Each flower eventually produces a large quantity of small seeds. This plant is thought to be one of the parents of Nicotiana tobacum, the plant used in modern tobacco production.

fields.title: Verbascum thapsus (Great or Common Mullein) Seeds
fields.text:
A packet of 1000 seeds. 
Great Mullein has been used since ancient times as a remedy for skin, throat and breathing ailments. It has long had a medicinal reputation, especially as an astringent and emollient, as it contains mucilage, several saponins, coumarin and glycosides. Dioscorides recommended it for diseases of the lung and it is now widely available in health and herbal stores. Non-medical uses have included dyeing and making torches. 
The plant's leaves, in addition to the seeds, have been reported to contain rotenone, although quantities are unknown 
This plant is a hairy biennial plant that can grow to 2 m or more tall. Its small yellow flowers are densely grouped on a tall stem, which bolts from a large rosette of leaves. It grows in a wide variety of habitats, but prefers well-lit disturbed soils, where it can appear soon after the ground receives light, from long-lived seeds that persist in the soil seed bank. It is a common weedy plant that spreads by prolifically producing seeds, but rarely becomes aggressively invasive, since its seed require open ground to germinate.

fields.title: Villages Quick Guide
fields.text:
villages > help

This is a brief guide to Villages and its terminology. 
[Work in Progress. Please send suggestions.]

Villages is an online economic system with:
- a social network of producers
- a marketplace of ads and private messages
- a payment system (credit clearing)
- an alternative currency (mutual credit)

It is based on the Ripple web-based mutual credit clearing system. Ripple models how people actually extend each other varying amounts of credit based on experience and trust. Then it finds paths of trust to enable strangers to pay each other. So unlike LETS, there is no collectivized debt exposure requiring arbitrary administration.

GLOSSARY  
Post - ad or announcement
Hour - unit and name of currency (time-based, divided with decimals)

Endorse - to extend a line of credit
Heart - hour-unit of line of credit

Acknowledge - to credit or pay 
Trusted - endorsed
Direct - unendorsed

Health - a person's unused percentage of your endorsement. A simple credit rating.
Overall Balance - total hours
Trusted Balance - trusted hours
Reputation - total hearts with you, both directly and indirectly through a person's trusted paths to you in the network.

When posting, use "Easy Categories". See next post or:
https://villages.cc/posts/148/

fields.title: Seeking input on new direction for Villages
fields.text:
A couple days ago, I watched a video of Alfie Kohn talking about how when you give students grades, they lose motivation for true learning.  Here's a small part:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EQt-ZI58wpw

It occurred to me that the same might be said of money:  When people work for money, they lose motivation for true giving.  

Maybe we should simplify Villages by getting rid of the monetary aspect entirely.  No hours, no hearts, just one way to indicate that you think someone's OK, no number attached.  Then we can find good people to help and help us out, and not worry about the numbers -- that was never the point anyway.  And if we happen to help someone out who never gives back, oh well, it's only helping them to come around eventually.  If people want to transact in cash, that's fine too, but ideally it would be by donation...

So...  What do you lovely people think?  Reply to this post, or in the discussion group I've set up:

https://groups.google.com/group/villagescc/

Thanks!

Ryan

fields.title: Evaluate IOPS
fields.text:
Evaluate the (interim) International Organization for a Participatory Society.

I'm willing to acknowledge your efforts at a rate of 1 Village Hour to 1 hour of evaluation. Let me know how much you are going to do and we will shake on the deal.

Tasks:

1. Evaluate the IOPS vision and write a paragraph describing your views on it:

    http://www.iopsociety.org/vision

2. If you agree with the IOPS vision, evaluate the IOPS structure and program and write a paragraph describing your views on it:

    http://www.iopsociety.org/structure-and-program

3. If you agree with the IOPS vision, structure and program, write a paragraph describing your reasons for either joining or not joining IOPS.

I'll want to publish what you write.  I'd appreciate if you have a blog, if you would publish it there as well.  If you aren't comfortable writing, I'd be happy if you record verbal explanations instead.  I would prefer if any writing you do is in your own voice, language and dialect or accent.  I'm not interested in "grammar" and punctuation.

fields.title: Game or Fiction Reading Reviews
fields.text:
I am offering my services as a reader for game or fiction texts. 

For game texts: I am a very critical reader and I am very good at finding areas in rules text where the rule seems ambiguous, or where there may be unusual side-effects.

For fiction: I can nitpick down to syntax and grammar pretty well, but I am not a professional editor. I am good at picking apart confusing dialogue or descriptions, and I'm good at noticing when loose ends aren't all tied up by the end.

Contact me and we'll talk about your specific needs.

fields.title: Game Design Consulting
fields.text: Many times when people get stuck in the game design process, it's because they've lost that initial burst of energy and excitement. Sometimes they know what the next steps are, but can't quite manage to get them done or find the drive they originally had. In such circumstances, I've had remarkably good luck with having in-depth conversations with designers about their project, their design goals, what "success" would feel like, their publication plans, cutting away the stuff that isn't working, and overall just helping people get back on track and rekindling some excitement about the project.

Provide me with a playtest-ready copy of your game and I can suggest that we play it there (supposing I can understand the game and find it at least moderately interesting). I can offer no guarantee that the game will be chosen to be played, and naturally expect no compensation in such case.

fields.title: Sci Fi artwork needed for RPG.
fields.text:
I'm looking for 5-10 pieces of sci-fi artwork to illustrate a 2nd print edition of the brilliant storygame While the World Ends.

The game is about ordinary people in a strange future, and what happens in their lives as the world changes around them.

I don't mind reusing art that has been published before in other contexts or even games, as long as I can get rights to use them in mine. I'm not in a real hurry, I'll need it before December, but of course earlier would be better. I'll take B/W or color, sketches, oil paintings, photo manipulations, pixel art or just about anything else.

I need pictures of people doing future stuff: like talking to aliens, working strange machinery, exploring alien worlds, carousing with robots, gazing at the stars while standing on a levitating platform, getting cybernetic implants in their brains, being chased by augmented chimps, guarding disintegrating androids praying with Tibetan monks   Stuff like that, things that happen in the future.

However, I'm not looking for pictures of people posing with future weapons.  While there is conflict in the game, armed conflict is rare. I've never had any PCs who spent time posing.

fields.title: Look at 110,000 Words of Lurid Sorcery (with minor mention of swords)
fields.text:
I have this... thing... that's been accumulating words the same way the cat box accumulates a nasty crust on the bottom.  The few people I've handed it off too have nodded and said "Wow, Gary, it's great!"  Hmm.  Bullhocky sez I.  So I'm looking for someone to tell me what's wrong with it - where (or even if) it can be improved, what I can do better, what parts of the forest I'm missing for being nose-planted against a tree.

I'll provide a PDF with line numbers, double-spaced, in whatever typeface and size you like.  I'll also provide you with this warning: it's (an as yet incomplete) first-person account of someone learning necromancy, and there is violence.  Several persons are flagrantly murdered in the course of the story thus far.  There is even some sexin'!  If you can trudge your way through a GRRM series, I can't imagine my story is much worse.

All I ask in return is a page, maybe, of honest commentary.  Even if that honest commentary is "unfit for fishwrap."

Thanks!

Edited to add: Commentary's coming back and I will shortly be deep in acknowledgement debt - so I'm suspending this want until I get some art out and balance things.  If I've emailed you a document, you'll be acknowledged.

fields.title: Looking for reviews and/or playtests of my game
fields.text:
EDIT: Thanks, all! I'm going to close this down, for now. If you've already set up a playtest, that's great, and I'll definitely still pay you for a report. But otherwise, I'm going to consider this version deprecated, and start writing the next version! :)

~~~

I have a game in development called "Far Horizons of the Unknown". (For those of you who read my Game Chef 2012 runner-up, this is its evolved form.) The one-sentence pitch: One of you will play a competent and interesting hero, while the rest of you build the mysterious and overwhelming world that hero is faced with. It's playable in 2 to 4 hours, with 3-5 players.

I've had some successful preliminary playtests, but I'd love some more feedback. 

I'm offering one hour in return for reading it and giving me your thoughts, or four hours for _playing_ it and giving me your thoughts. (If you record it as well, I'll give you six hours instead. If any of your other players are on Villages, they get two hours for playing, and another two if they also give me their thoughts.) You can feel free to either post comments somewhere online and send me the link, or else just send them directly to me, either way.

There are actually two playsets currently released. For my purposes, either one counts as "the game". You definitely don't have to read/play both of them.

The first is called "The Shadows of the Trees", and is set in a pretty standard sword-and-sorcery world:

http://semielgames.wordpress.com/2012/07/06/the-shadows-of-the-trees-playtest-document/

The second is called "The Coyotes of Chicago", and is about mysterious things happening to urban coyote researchers in Chicago:

http://semielgames.wordpress.com/2012/07/25/the-coyotes-of-chicago-playtest-document/

fields.title: Read through/Editing/Playtesting [want]
fields.text:
I've been developing a game that uses learning a different language (Korean in this case) as the resolution mechanic. The game is about magicians in a boarding school living and studying together. Players earn drama points by building and putting their characters in scenes that emotionally traumatize them in some way. Drama points are then used to fuel casting spells and in order to cast spells you must speak Korean.

fields.title: MOVEMBER
fields.text:
I am looking for 1 or 2 hour donations sponsorship for my effort to support Male health awareness. 

I am fundraising for http://ca.movember.com/about/ It is a month long race to grow the best moustache and raise awareness for Men's Health. 

Follow my progress at http://mobro.co/darinmbicknell. I will post in mospace if you donate through Villages. I will be working to promote Men's Health at every opportunity and I will get myself an appointment for a Men's Health Checkup as part of the spirit of Movember and as I am getting longer in the tooth it is time to get checked every year. 

So any and all donations are welcome. 1 hour would be nice if I make it the whole the month without going nuts and shaving off the stache... and 2 hours if I also get my check up done in November.  http://ca.movember.com/mens-health/ .

OVERVIEW OF MOVEMBER

During November each year, Movember is responsible for the sprouting of moustaches on thousands of men’s faces, in Canada and around the world. With their “Mo’s”, these men raise vital funds and awareness for men's health, specifically prostate cancer and male mental health initiatives.

On Movember 1st, guys register at Movember.com with a clean-shaven face. For the rest of the month, these selfless and generous men, known as Mo Bros, groom, trim and wax their way into the annals of fine moustachery. Supported by the women in their lives, Mo Sistas, Movember Mo Bros raise funds by seeking out sponsorship for their Mo-growing efforts.

Mo Bros effectively become walking, talking billboards for the 30 days of November. Through their actions and words, they raise awareness by prompting private and public conversation around the often ignored issue of men’s health.

At the end of the month, Mo Bros and Mo Sistas celebrate their gallantry and valor by either throwing their own Movember party or attending one of the infamous Gala Partés held around the world by Movember, for Movember.  

Movember - a global movement

Since its humble beginnings in Melbourne Australia, Movember has grown to become a truly global movement inspiring more than 1.9 Million Mo Bros and Mo Sistas to participate with formal campaigns in Australia, New Zealand, the US, Canada, the UK, South Africa, Ireland, Finland, the Netherlands, Spain, Denmark, Norway, Belgium and the Czech Republic. In addition, Movember is aware of Mo Bros and Mo Sistas supporting the campaign and men’s health cause across the globe, from Russia to Dubai, Hong Kong to Antarctica, Rio de Janeiro to Mumbai, and everywhere in between.

No matter the country or city, Movember will continue to work to change established habits and attitudes men have about their health, to educate men about the health risks they face, and to act on that knowledge, thereby increasing the chances of early detection, diagnosis and effective treatment.

In 2011, over 854,000 Mo Bros and Mo Sistas around the world got on board, raising $125.7 million CAD.

No.

When you go into a bank and borrow a large amount of money to buy a small amount of house, that money doesn't come from somebody else's savings.

fields.title: Leo Tolstoy wrote
fields.text:
I ask and want nothing today, other than to share a quote that this network reminded me of: 

“Good consists not in the giving of money, it consists in the loving intercourse of men. This alone is needed. Whatever may be the outcome of this, any thing will be better than the present state of things. Then let the final act of our enumerators and directors be to distribute a hundred twenty-kopek pieces to those who have no food; and this will be not a little, not so much because the hungry will have food, because the directors and enumerators will conduct themselves in a humane manner towards a hundred poor people. How are we to compute the possible results which will accrue to the balance of public morality from the fact that, instead of the sentiments of irritation, anger, and envy which we arouse by reckoning the hungry, we shall awaken in a hundred instances a sentiment of good, which will be communicated to a second and a third, and an endless wave which will thus be set in motion and flow between men? And this is a great deal.”

I want to bring to your attention a great treasure in our community of whom you might not be aware.

I am referring to David Ream, MKP brother who lives in Seaview and who is in my humble opinion the best bodyworker I have ever experienced.

Since I have been living here in Puna, I have experienced a number of bodyworkers, but David is in a class all his own. Never before have I experienced a bodyworker who has integrated so many different modalities in his own, intuitive,  methodical approach to heal my body: chiropractic, Rolfing, Thai, a combination of deep tissue, muscle and skeletal work  that leaves me feeling far more energized. My body feels like it has returned to my 30s.  

His fee is $1 a minute. I opt for 2 hr sessions and I always pay him more than his ask because of the value I receive from each session. 

As a community, I believe we are here to support each other and David's incalculable gifts, I believe, will bring you to a new level of well-being.

fields.description: If you have a creative endeavor that you could use some clarity on, or direction from a creative professional, I would be glad to host you for a 45 minute consultation. In these sessions, you are posed prompts, and offered reflection and guidance by me. Results include a refreshed sense of clarity about the mission statement and priorities involved in what you are creating, a greater sense of the priority steps to take it to the next level, and a general action plan on what is yours to do and who (if applicable) you may need to find to collaborate with. A single session can offer a great deal on its own, or you have the option to book multiple visits at once for a reduced rate if we determine it may be in your best interest. It all truly depends on your unique scenario.
fields.title: Creative Consultations

fields.description:
I'd like to offer private one-on-one lessons in the software program of your choice, including:
- Adobe Photoshop – photo retouching, digital & print layout such as banners & flyers.
- Adobe Illustrator – vector illustration, graphical & geometry-based art that can scale infinitely.
- Adobe InDesign – digital & print layout, optimal for ads, flyers, menus, books & ebooks, stationary & business cards, etc.

The efficiency of learning these skills in this way is very high, as the alternative would be to enroll in extensive courses in-person or online, or to spend many years exploring ins and outs of the way these programs work. 

A bonus is that you will inherently learn some design principles from me as we run through sample layouts or design your chosen piece in real time. 

Price includes 1-hour lessons. Reduced rate if booking 6 or more sessions at once.

I have been using the Adobe Creative Suite for over 15-years now as a student of art & design, and in my 11-year professional tenure as a graphic artist.
fields.title: Learn Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator, Indesign

The sacral chakra is blocked by fear, especially by the fear of death. This is why it can feel so scary to speak our truth or sing our song publicly. fields.description:
Introduction to your unique energetic imprint through the lens of Human Design.
Discover tools to experiment with a practical and logical way to attune your decision making process based on your unique and consistent life force.  

Human design is a synthesis of modern genetic science, ancient iching, astrology and the kabalah to see the unique energetic signature within our body as the true authority in the physical plane as the personality and mind are in service as the research and development department to give the body.  Each human is unique and differentiated in its cognition as a specific frame of reference in which consciousness is seeing through.  We have been conditioned in life to see through generalized filters that serve a homogenized outcome.  it is becoming more and more obvious that we are here as beautiful individuals with a specific contribution to the world, without purpose or agenda aside from the intrinsic presence of simply being our self.  

This attunement offers a view into the practical tools to see where our masks are prevalent and  where we have judged and silenced the natural consistency of our life force, that hijacks our ability to truly allow our body the gift of being on its most natural alignment and trajectory free of resistance.  

We have entered a deep cleansing of frequency on our earthly existence and our race is mutating into new form genetically, moving from the last 400 year cycle of cooperation and contractual obligations into the empowerment of the individual spirit within each of us.  It is the time of learning to truly honor and love ourselves as we are, and as we see through our unique lens of experience so that we find a trust in our own inner authority without the need to rely on external agendas of the old story.  You are the star in your movie, the exalted life force of creation speaking through your experience.  Beyond the vanity of the story we realize that we are all in this together, and as we release the comparison models of the past we can step into the co-creative beauty of acceptance that being who we are is the best gift we have to offer.

fields.description:
With love and reverence, I offer private and group attunement for Reiki in the Usui tradition - Level 1 (self-healing) and Level 2 (sharing Reiki with others).

I’ve been practicing Reiki for 8 years, and have been a Reiki Master attuning and training others for the past 3 years.

Feel free to check out my website and Instagram to get a feel for me, and welcome to connect if you feel the call.

http://www.stephanielyralin.com
Instagram @stephanielyralin
Phone: 808-896-1335

Reiki is not only a beautiful system of energy healing, but also a spiritual system of enlightenment.

Level 1 is 6 VH and requires 2-3 hours of time together.
Level 2 is 8 VH and requires an additional 2-3 hours of time together.
We can negotiate number of meetings and location.

Included in the attunement and training is a PDF of Level 1 and 2 Reiki manuals from my teacher, and two follow up videos (pre-recorded).

I love sharing Reiki and would love to attune and train more practitioners in Puna, so we can support those in need (especially elderly and sick) with our love and healing touch.

Blessings love and gratitude,
Lyra
fields.title: Reiki Level 1 and Level 2
